                <section>
                  <title>Tech in Asia</title>
                  <subtitle>Japan’s Lonely Child</subtitle>
                  <chapter>
                    <paragraph>On March 4th, 2016, Mercari, a peer-to-peer marketplace app,
                      has claimed the title of Japan’s first pre-IPO startup
                      unicorn after raising 8.4 billion yen (about $75 million)
                      at a valuation of over $ 1 billion. This is the Tokyo-based
                      company’s first Series D. Launched in 2013, Mercari lets users
                      buy and sell products including fashion, electronics and handmade items.</paragraph>
                    </chapter>
